article.headline: Buffalos win WBCA Classic
article.linkText: Colorado rebuffs Notre Dame in overtime
article.story:
BOULDER, Colo. (AP) -- Emily Waner hit a 3-pointer with 12.6 seconds left in overtime, and Tera Bjorklund had 21 points and eight rebounds as No. 20 Colorado beat No. 15 Notre Dame 67-63 Saturday night in the championship game of the WBCA Classic.

Waner, who had 10 points, had given Colorado (2-0) a 62-61 lead
with a 3-pointer with 1:55 left. Teresa Borton converted two free
throws to put Notre Dame (1-1) ahead 63-62, but Jacqueline Batteast
turned the ball over in the last three seconds after Waner's
3-pointer.

Le'Tania Severe led Notre Dame with 14 points. Batteast added 13
points and 10 rebounds.

The Buffaloes sent the game into overtime with a 3-pointer at
the buzzer from Veronica Johns-Richardson, tying the score at 55.

Megan Duffy had a chance to seal the win for Notre Dame with 19
seconds left in regulation but missed the front end of one-and-one
free throws.

Severe and Duffy had 10 points each.

Notre Dame led 37-33 at halftime after opening the game with a
12-0 run. The Buffaloes came as close as 34-33 after two free
throws by Kate Fagan with 20 seconds remaining, but Severe got an
offensive rebound and beat the buzzer with a 3-pointer.
